hopobject.body: What do you want to do when you've finished? beryldrugs.com The two-seater concept car is a collaboration between the Caterham Group’s various divisions, including its Formula One team, and uses a carbon-fibre body and 2.0-litre engine. The Ford Duratec-based unit produces 237bhp, meaning the AeroSeven can accelerate from 0-62mph in under 4sec. It is fitted with a manual six-speed gearbox and new fully variable traction and launch control, as well as a race-derived anti-lock braking system, which Caterham says is the subject of a feasibility study.
